-- Canada's Nova Scotia Reports Deficit of $234 Million for 2009-2010 Year
-- Greg Quinn
-- 2010-07-29T14:15:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/canada-s-nova-scotia-reports-deficit-of-234-million-for-2009-2010-year.html

          
          
             Nova Scotia said the last fiscal
year’s budget deficit was C$241.9 million ($234 million), lower
than an April estimate of C$488.4 million.  
 Finance Minister Graham Steele gave the new figure for the
2009-2010 fiscal year on the government’s website today.  
